Several readers sent us links to an AP story about a pair of Kansas City
booksellers who [0]staged a book bonfire, claiming to protest declining
literacy. The story doesn't convey a sure sense of the booksellers'
motives for what could, in fact, be a PR stunt or a subtle act of
extortion against book lovers â€” it does mention that people were buying
books out of the piles awaiting immolation. The [1]bookstore's own site
tries to sound sincere, but it offers visitors a chance to save books
from the flames for $1 each plus postage.

