| NASA To Release Landsat 7 Data On the Web                          |
|   from the planetary-legacy dept.                                  |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday May 28, @23:03 (Space)               |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/29/0045223      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

UAVThumper writes "The US Geological Survey homepage is featuring an
article about the [0]upcoming release of select Landsat 7 image data (on
June 4) at glovis.usgs.gov or earthexplorer.usgs.gov. This is to be a
pilot project for a larger effort called the Landsat Data Continuity
Mission, whose end result looks like a version of Google Earth using
Landsat data. Seven Landsat satellites were launched over a period of 27
years, the last in 1999. More on Landsat can be found [1]here on
Wikipedia or [2]here at the official NASA Page."

