|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/29/0152250              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "The New Zealand Ministry of Education has
[0]declined to renew a licensing deal for MS Office on 25,000 Macintosh
computers in the country's schools. The Education Minister has suggested
that schools use the free alternative [1]NeoOffice. The article quotes a
school principal who pointed out that the NeoOffice website warns users
to expect problems and bugs: 'That's not the sort of software we should
be expecting kids in New Zealand to be using.'" Schools are free to buy
their own copies of Office. A blog on the New Zealand Herald site argues
that the Ministry should have [2]paid Microsoft this time, but not
renewed the deal and instead developed a transition plan to open source.

