| RPG Devs Should Beware MMOGs                                       |
|   from the going-to-eat-your-lunch dept.                           |
|   posted by Zonk on Tuesday May 29, @16:30 (Role Playing (Games))  |
|   http://games.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/29/2024248        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

CVG is reporting on comments made by Obsidian CEO Feargus Urquhart. In an
interview with the site, he points out that traditional PC RPG developers
are in danger of [0]permanently losing out to the developers of Massively
Multiplayer Online Games. "He believes it's key that developers of
non-MMO RPGs look closely at what the genre offers over MMORPGs to ensure
the RPG genre doesn't lose out to the increasingly popular massively
multiplayer online world. 'I think those of us that make non-MMO RPGs
need to look at what a single-player/small multiplayer RPG can do that
MMOs can't and spend our time and effort on those things', Urquhart said.
"

