| Screencasts of Installing MythTV Via MythDora 4.0                  |
|   from the simple-as-it-gets dept.                                 |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday May 29, @18:20 (Media)              |
|   http://linux.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/29/2244233        |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]peterdaly writes "[1]MythDora 4 is a MythTV 'in-a-box' style
distribution based on Fedora Core 6. With the help of a [2]RedHat
employee and author Jarod Wilson, MythDora 4 has made great strides in
hardware compatibility and ease of installation. It is designed to format
your hard drive and install everything needed for a fully functional
MythTV System. MythPVR.com has created a three-part screencast of the
installation process covering [3]MythDora installation, [4]configuration,
and [5]MythTV setup. If you have had problem installing MythTV in the
past due to hardware compatibility issues, it might be time to give it
another chance."

