+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| The Secrets of Firefox about:config                                |
|   from the Mozilla-fu dept.                                        |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday May 29, @19:45 (Mozilla)            |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/29/2333256              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

jcatcw writes "While Firefox is very customizable, many of its settings
aren't in the Options. Each setting is named and stored as a string,
integer, or Boolean in a file called prefs.js and accessed via
about:config from the nav bar. [0]Computerworld provides instructions on
20 tweaks for speeding up page loads, making tabs behave, reducing memory
drain, and generally making the interface act the way you want it to.
Customization also comes through [1]the must-have FF extensions (but be
sure to [2]skip these)."

